wikipedia_page.main: John Bosworth (May 1836 – 27 September 1917) was a politician in the early days of the Colony of South Australia.

link_mentions.page: Members of the South Australian House of Assembly, 1875–1878
response: : Wooroora MHA James Pearce resigned on 27 July 1875. John Bosworth won the resulting by-election on 7 August.
